// Build settings for the bundled inference engine side-car.
//
// The Dart side (lib/core/ai/llama_cpp_bindings.dart) opens libllama
// at runtime via dart:ffi. For the lookup to succeed in a notarised
// .app bundle, libllama.dylib must live inside Runner.app/Contents/
// Frameworks and be referenced with @rpath/.
//
// CI drops the universal-binary libllama.dylib into native/macos/
// before invoking `flutter build macos`. The build script below copies
// it into the .app bundle. When the file is absent, the FFI lookup
// returns null and the app falls back to "Connect to existing engine"
// — the .app still builds and runs.
//
// Apply this xcconfig from Runner.xcodeproj's Runner target via
// "Configuration → Based on configuration file" so that the search
// paths line up regardless of debug / release.
//
// See native/README.md for build instructions for libllama.dylib.

LD_RUNPATH_SEARCH_PATHS = $(inherited) @executable_path/../Frameworks
FRAMEWORK_SEARCH_PATHS = $(inherited) $(SRCROOT)/../native/macos
LIBRARY_SEARCH_PATHS = $(inherited) $(SRCROOT)/../native/macos
